########################################################################################################################
# Help for recent directories
########################################################################################################################
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
[CTRL + X THEN J] or  rd : navigate to a recently visited directory
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Displays a numbered list of the most recently visited directories (most recent first).
Type a number and press Enter to jump there instantly.
Home (~) and root (/) are excluded from the list — they are too generic to be useful.
Directories that have been removed since the last visit are skipped automatically.

Example output:
  1) /var/log/nginx
  2) /etc/nixlper
  3) /home/user/projects/myapp/src
  Jump to [1-3] (Enter to cancel):

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Configuration (via nconf or ~/.config/nixlper/nixlper.conf):

  NIXLPER_RECENT_DIRS_MAX    int    20    Maximum number of recent directories to remember
  NIXLPER_RECENT_DIRS_FILE   path         History file (default: ~/.local/share/nixlper/recent_dirs)

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
